<title>USA: Silicon Graphics buys ParaGraph firm.</title>
<headline>Silicon Graphics buys ParaGraph firm.</headline>
<dateline>MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. 1997-05-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Silicon Graphics Inc. said Wednesday it has signed a definitive agreement to acquire ParaGraph International, a company which makes three-dimensional Internet software for personal computers.</p>
<p>Silicon Graphics also said it is establishing a new unit, Cosmo Software, which will focus on the fast-emerging market for 3-D Internet software which runs on multiple computer systems.</p>
<p>ParaGraph will be integrated into the new Cosmo unit.</p>
<p>Financial terms of the acquisition were not disclosed.</p>
<p>ParaGraph International is headquartered in Campbell, Calif., with research and development there and in Moscow.</p>
